<p><b>What is the main theme of there there?</b> "There There" is a powerful novel that weaves together the stories of twelve characters from the urban Native American community in Oakland, California. Through their interconnected narratives, the book explores themes of identity, belonging, and the impact of historical trauma on indigenous peoples.</p>
